## What exists and works now

- **`.github/workflows/kaggle-art-batch.yml`** — full batch orchestration: auth (prefers
  `KAGGLE_USERNAME`/`KAGGLE_KEY` secrets, falls back to committed `.kaggle/kaggle.json`),
  manifest staging, dataset create/version, readiness wait, kernel push, 60s status polls
  with 90-min timeout, output download, error-log tail, artifact upload. Trigger manually
  (workflow_dispatch).
- **`.github/workflows/kaggle-kernel-log.yml`** — diagnostics: dumps the full kernel log
  via the Kaggle API (no multi-GB download) and prints per-image pixel statistics.
- **`tools/art/kernel/generate.py`** — currently configured: Z-Image-Turbo, fp16 weights,
  `device_map="balanced"` over 2×T4, layerwise fp32 compute (the part that crashes),
  fp32 VAE, incremental generation log, OOM-safe packaging.
- **Kaggle side** — dataset `abordage-art-manifest` v1 (note: contains the junk-line
  manifest; the cleaned manifest uploads on the next run thanks to fix #9), kernel at
  version 7, account phone-verified (internet + T4 GPUs work).

Timings observed: weights download+load ≈ 8–12 min; generation ≈ 35 s/image in fp16.

